{"blocks":[{"key":"9d8m3","text":"Several versions of slaking index calculations have been suggested. The slaking index originally recommended by Fajardo et al. (2016) involved fitting a rise-to-threshold (Goempertz function) model to timeseries of aggregate area, and computing the function's limit as the slaking index (SI). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ccbsa","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"92jkc","text":"Flynn et al. (2020) recommended instead computing the observed change in aggregate area over time:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8bov7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"at7gq","text":"        SI600 = (A600 - A0)/A0","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":8,"length":5},{"style":"italic","offset":17,"length":9},{"style":"italic","offset":28,"length":2},{"style":"sub","offset":18,"length":3},{"style":"sub","offset":25,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":29,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7avog","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"20hq9","text":"where A0 is the initial projected area of the dry aggregate and A600 is the projected
